                <p>Studies show that during intense physical activity, a lot of liquid reserves in the body can be consumed before the individual feel thirsty. Without these reserves, the body suffers from dehydration. In addition to age, the ability to perceive the symptoms of dehydration decreases. So there's no way: even those who are not water fan should surrender its powers.</p>
