                <h2>News and Events</h2>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h4>How much water needed?</h4>
                    <div class="imgdireita"><img src="img/agua.jpg" alt=""></div>
                <p>Who has not heard that we need to take at least 2 liters of water a day for the body to function well?</p>
                <p>But is this is the appropriate amount for all individuals?</p>
                <p>How to know how much water should we drink a day?</p>
                <p>In fact, the amount of water to be consumed depends on a number of factors ranging from the amount of exercise performed to room temperature where estamos.A following describes some of the factors which influence and determine the amount of water that must drink daily:</p>
                <p>** Level of physical activity: Who is everyday needs more water than someone who does three times a week hiking. Therefore, the more intense physical activity performed, the greater the amount of water required. It is also important to drink water during and after physical activity.</p>
                <p>** Climate: Who lives in hot cities, needs more water than those who live in colder places. We also need more water in summer when sweat more and thus lose more water than in winter.</p>
                <p>** Metabolism: Who has a higher metabolism needs more water than those with slower metabolism.</p>
                <p>** Weight: 100kg A person needs more water than a 50 kilograms. The greater the weight, the greater the need of water.</p>
                <p>** Diet: If you eat too much salt, will need more water than those who eat more fruits and vegetables, which are rich in water.</p>
                <p>** General condition: Some physical conditions interfere with the need of water. If you have fever, for example, should increase fluid intake. The same tip applies to those who have episodes of diarrhea or vomiting. To replace lost fluid, opt for broths and soups instead of sugary liquids. Some diseases such as renal failure, for example, require limiting the amount of water intake.</p>
                <p>** Drinking: If you drink alcohol, try alternating alcoholic drinks with water. The trick is to have a glass of water after every drink, since alcohol helps dehydrate the body. For the avoidance of doubt, note how often you urinate and the color of your urine. Ideally, it is amarelo-clara.Se urine is dark yellow with a strong odor and you are going less often than usual to the bathroom, it is a sign that you are eating little water. Take two cups of water to hydrate.</p>
