                 <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h4>Five good reasons not to stop taking water</h4>
                    <div class="imgdireita"><img src="img/copocomagua.jpg" alt=""></div>
                <p>There is no way to live without water. It represents 40% to 80% of the total weight of the human being, and vital organ functions depend on it to be fully realized.</p>
                <p>To supply all the body's needs must be taken on average two liters of water every day. The nutritionist Camila Leonel da Paulista School of Medicine, Unifesp (Federal University of São Paulo) explains that, over 24 hours, we lost about two liters of water through perspiration, urine, breath and other activities that maintain vital functions. "The body does not have any reservations or conditions for water storage. It is essential that your spare is daily to maintain health and basic body functions. In household measures, that amount is eight glasses ".</p>
                <p>"What often happens is that many people expect to have thirsty to drink water. Thirst is a warning signal to the body's need for water. It appears when the amount of fluid in the body is already below the desired level. So do not wait to get thirsty and your body go with the levels of águana reservation. Replenish your body frequently, "emphasizes Leonel.</p>
                <p>Dehydrated individuals have less blood volume than normal, which ends up hindering the functioning of the heart. The lack of water can cause weakness, dizziness, headache, fatigue, and if it is too long, lead to death.</p>
                <p>One tip is: always have a bottle of water at hand, for fluid replacement should be frequent and independent of sense of thirst. Also, if two liters of water seem too, know that part of the daily intake can be supplied to other sources, such as juices, coconut water, milk, fruit, teas and soups.</p>
                <p>If these details have not yet convinced about the importance of rigorously drink the required amount of water a day, here are five other benefits of water:</p>
                <p>* It regulates body temperature - During the exercise or when the weather is too hot, the water is released from the body by sweating to regulate temperature and prevent our body too warm or suffer rapid temperature changes.</p>
                <p>* Detoxifies the body - It assists in the prevention and treatment of urinary infection because the liquid stimulates trips to the bathroom, which helps to "clean up" the urinary tract. In partnership with the action of dietary fiber, water helps to form and hydrate the stool, preventing it from drying and, consequently, cause constipation. It also assists in respiration, it dilutes the mucous, facilitating the expectoration of pulmonary residues.</p>
                <p>* Absorption and Transport of nutrients - Water aids in absorption of nutrients and glucose. In addition, the fluid helps in the transport of these substances by the blood stream and distribution to various parts of the body.</p>
                <p>* Slimming - In addition to reducing water retention because it puts the kidneys to work, water also brings feeling of satiety. So drink two or three glasses before a meal helps control appetite. Not to mention that has no calories.</p>
